---
import "~/global.css";
import "~/mist.css";
import HeadCommon from "~/components/HeadCommon.astro";
import ProfileImage from "~/assets/profile-picture.png";
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import Download from "~/icons/Download.astro";

const ogImage = new URL(ProfileImage.src, Astro.site);

export const prerender = true;
---

<html dir="ltr" lang="en">
<head>
	<HeadCommon
		title={"CV"}
		image={{
			src: ogImage.href,
			alt: "profile image",
		}}
		description="Kostiantyn Doichev's CV"
	/>
	<style>
		@media print {
			@page {
				margin: 2cm;
				size: A4;
			}

			section {
				break-inside: avoid;
			}

			header {
				break-after: avoid;
			}

			a {
				text-decoration: underline;
				color: black;
			}
		}

	</style>
</head>
<body>
<main class="container mx-auto font-mono print:w-full">
	<div class="py-4 flex justify-end print:hidden">
		<a data-component="button" download="" href="/doichev-kostiantyn-full-stack.pdf">
			<Download class="mr-1 size-5" />
			Download PDF
		</a>
	</div>
	<div class="bg-primary-foreground sm:px-8 pb-4 pt-4 print:p-0" id="cv">
		<header class="flex gap-x-3 mb-5 print:mb-3">
			<div>
				<Picture src={ProfileImage} alt="profile" formats={["webp", "png"]}
						 class="aspect-square rounded-2xl bg-primary-foreground object-cover w-20 h-20 print:w-12 print:h-12" />
			</div>
			<div>
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl print:text-lg">Kostiantyn Doichev</h1>
				<h3 class="text-xl text-muted-foreground print:text-sm print:text-muted-foreground">
					Software Engineer
				</h3>
			</div>
		</header>
		<section class="hidden print:block mb-3">
			<p class="text-sm">
				The web version of this CV is available at <a
				class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
				href={Astro.url}>doichevkostia.dev/cv</a>
			</p>
		</section>
		<section class="mb-5 print:mb-2">
			<h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl print:text-base print:mb-1 font-semibold">About Me</h2>
			<p class="print:text-sm">
				I really like solving different problems that users have, those could be B2C web applications,
				custom internal apps or developer tooling.
				Over time, I've learned the importance of balancing challenging engineering tasks with simpler, faster
				decisions that meet business needs and allow for progress.
				Additionally, I realized, that the value of the software engineer is not in being the React Andy
				and knowing only one tool,
				but being able to figure stuff out even in an environment where you have never been before.
				This includes taking on different roles within a project, leading a team, engaging with the customers,
				knowing when to be the flag carrier and making a decision, instead of having hours of
				discussions and landing on an unsatisfying compromise.
				<br>
				<br>
				My core value as an engineer is that I <strong>solve</strong> problems, no matter what they are.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section class="mb-5 print:mb-2">
			<h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl print:text-base print:mb-1 font-semibold">Contact</h2>
			<p class="print:text-sm">
				I'm originally from Kyiv, Ukraine, and currently live in Leuven, Belgium.
				<br>
				My website is <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
								 href="https://doichevkostia.dev">doichevkostia.dev</a>
				<br>
				My GitHub profile is <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
										href="https://github.com/doichev-kostia">github.com/doichev-kostia</a>
				<br>
				My email is <code class="font-medium font-ligatures-none">doichev.kostia@gmail.com</code>
			</p>
		</section>
		<section class="mb-5 print:mb-2">
			<h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl print:text-base print:mb-1 font-semibold">Expectations</h2>
			<div>
				<p class="print:text-sm">
					I would like to have the full-stack role with the primary focus on the <strong>back-end</strong>
					side. I also love exploring fields like infrastructure or systems programming.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="mb-5 print:mb-2">
			<h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl print:text-base print:mb-1 font-semibold">Open-source contributions</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc pl-4 print:text-sm">
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created an issue <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
										href="https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/22688">#22688</a> and
					proposed a workaround in <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
										 href="https://github.com/microsoft/playwright">microsoft/playwright</a>
				</li>
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created a pr <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
									href="https://github.com/sst/sst/pull/5045">#5045</a> in <a
					class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium" href="https://github.com/sst/sst">sst/sst</a>
				</li>
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created an issue <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
									href="https://github.com/swc-project/swc-node/issues/743">#743</a> with a fix in <a
					class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium" href="https://github.com/swc-project/swc-node">swc-project/swc-node</a>
				</li>
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created a pr <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
									href="https://github.com/mcollina/reusify/pull/13">#13</a> in <a
					class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium" href="https://github.com/mcollina/reusify">mcollina/reusify</a>
				</li>
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created a pr <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
									href="https://github.com/PacktPublishing/Accelerating-Server-Side-Development-with-Fastify/pull/52">#52</a> in <a
					class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium" href="https://github.com/PacktPublishing/Accelerating-Server-Side-Development-with-Fastify">PacktPublishing/Accelerating-Server-Side-Development-with-Fastify</a>
				</li>
				<li class="print:text-sm">
					Created an issue <a class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium"
									href="https://github.com/integrations/slack/issues/1630">#1630</a> in <a
					class="underline underline-offset-4 font-medium" href="https://github.com/integrations/slack">integrations/slack</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl print:text-base print:mb-1 font-semibold">Experience</h2>
			<div>
				<h3 class="text-xl print:text-base">Panenco</h3>
				<h4 class="text-base text-muted-foreground print:text-sm">Software Engineer</h4>
				<p class="mb-1 print:text-sm">
					<time datetime="2021-11">November 2021</time>
					- <span>Present</span>
				</p>
				<p class="print:text-sm">
					As a full-stack engineer, with primary focus on back-end development, I've done the following:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-4 print:text-sm">
					<li class="print:text-sm">Developed server-side applications using TypeScript with Node.js, C# with ASP .Net Core.</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Developed client-side applications using TypeScript and React.js</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Created CLI apps and tooling using Go.</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Was actively involved in building the application infrastructure using tools like Pulumi or SST,
						alongside with creating CI pipelines (GitHub actions).
					</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Built different features from simple CRUDs to more complex durable workflows, communication
						services
						using WebSockets
					</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Optimized CPU/Memory heavy operations in the app</li>
					<li class="print:text-sm">Worked primarily with SQL database, PostgreSQL in particular</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

</main>
</body>
</html>
